#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.190"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.190:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.190:0.2"
msgid "19. Araññavagga"
msgstr "19. Wilderness Dwellers"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.190:0.3"
msgid "190. Pattapiṇḍikasutta"
msgstr "190. Those Who Eat Only From the Almsbowl"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.190:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcime, bhikkhave, pattapiṇḍikā."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, there are these five kinds of people who eat only from the "
"almsbowl."

msgctxt "an5.190:1.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.190:1.3"
msgid ""
"Mandattā momūhattā pattapiṇḍiko hoti, pāpiccho icchāpakato pattapiṇḍiko "
"hoti, ummādā cittakkhepā pattapiṇḍiko hoti, ‘vaṇṇitaṃ buddhehi "
"buddhasāvakehī’ti pattapiṇḍiko hoti, appicchataṃyeva nissāya santuṭṭhiṃyeva "
"nissāya sallekhaṃyeva nissāya pavivekaṃyeva nissāya idamatthitaṃyeva nissāya "
"pattapiṇḍiko hoti."
msgstr ""
"A person may eat only from the almsbowl because of stupidity and folly. Or "
"because of wicked desires, being naturally full of desires. Or because of "
"madness and mental disorder. Or because it is praised by the Buddhas and "
"their disciples. Or for the sake of having few wishes, for the sake of "
"contentment, self-effacement, seclusion, and simplicity."

msgctxt "an5.190:1.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca pattapiṇḍikā."
msgstr "These are the five kinds of people who eat only from the almsbowl."

msgctxt "an5.190:1.5"
msgid ""
"Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ pattapiṇḍikānaṃ yvāyaṃ pattapiṇḍiko "
"appicchataṃyeva nissāya santuṭṭhiṃyeva nissāya sallekhaṃyeva nissāya "
"pavivekaṃyeva nissāya idamatthitaṃyeva nissāya pattapiṇḍiko hoti, ayaṃ "
"imesaṃ pañcannaṃ pattapiṇḍikānaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca mokkho ca uttamo ca "
"pavaro ca."
msgstr ""
"But the person who eats only from the almsbowl for the sake of having few "
"wishes is the foremost, best, chief, highest, and finest of the five."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.221"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.190:2.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gavā khīraṃ, khīramhā dadhi, dadhimhā navanītaṃ, "
"navanītamhā sappi, sappimhā sappimaṇḍo, sappimaṇḍo tattha aggamakkhāyati;"
msgstr ""
"From a cow comes milk, from milk comes curds, from curds come butter, from "
"butter comes ghee, and from ghee comes cream of ghee. And the cream of ghee "
"is said to be the best of these."

msgctxt "an5.190:2.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, imesaṃ pañcannaṃ pattapiṇḍikānaṃ yvāyaṃ "
"pattapiṇḍiko appicchataṃyeva nissāya santuṭṭhiṃyeva nissāya sallekhaṃyeva "
"nissāya pavivekaṃyeva nissāya idamatthitaṃyeva nissāya pattapiṇḍiko hoti, "
"ayaṃ imesaṃ pañcannaṃ pattapiṇḍikānaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca mokkho ca uttamo ca "
"pavaro cā”ti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, the person who eats only from the almsbowl for the sake of "
"having few wishes is the foremost, best, chief, highest, and finest of the "
"five.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.190:2.3"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.190:2.4"
msgid "Araññavaggo catuttho."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.190:3.1"
msgid "Araññaṃ cīvaraṃ rukkha,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.190:3.2"
msgid "Susānaṃ abbhokāsikaṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.190:3.3"
msgid "Nesajjaṃ santhataṃ ekāsanikaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.190:3.4"
msgid "Khalupacchāpiṇḍikena cāti."
msgstr ""
